# Python
# uv stubs auto-generated by Replit's packager — UNUSED here: the build is
# pip + requirements/*.txt (Docker) and `uv pip install -r ...` (VM deploy),
# neither of which reads pyproject.toml/uv.lock. Tracking them made DO App
# Platform auto-detect a uv buildpack and fail with
# "python version required when uv package manager is used: invalid argument".
# Keep them untracked so a regenerated stub never re-leaks to GitHub/DO.
# ANCHORED with a leading slash so backend/pyproject.toml (pytest/ruff config)
# stays tracked.
/pyproject.toml
/uv.lock
/backend/uv.lock
quick-id/backups/
# Quick-ID local PII backups (never commit)
# Replit chat-attached assets (screenshots, pasted images, etc.) — auto-uploaded
# Secure storage (encrypted ID photos, etc. — never commit)
# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.
# Sensitive tokens/credentials (NOT .env files - those are needed for deployment)
# stress runs and must NOT leak.
