# --- Two-repl shared-origin de-conflict (Task #5) ---
# This GitHub origin is fed by TWO Replit repls: this one (mobile/static,
# -syroce host) and a separate VM web+backend repl (-1 host). The paths below
# legitimately DIFFER per repl, so tracking them caused a merge conflict on
# every GitHub Pull. Each repl now keeps its own local copy.
#   IMPORTANT: this must be applied in BOTH repls. .gitignore alone does NOT
#   untrack already-committed files — the operator must run, once per repl:
#     git rm -r --cached .replit frontend/build .agents/memory && git commit
#   See docs/ops/TWO_REPL_SYNC_DECONFLICT.md for the full operator procedure.
#
# .replit: deployment block / workflows / userenv differ per repl (this repl
# stays deploymentTarget="static"; the VM repl stays "vm"). Untracking also
# removes plaintext userenv secrets from future commits.
.replit
# frontend/build: generated React SPA build. The VM repl serves it and must
# regenerate it at deploy time (cd frontend && yarn build); this static repl
# deploys mobile/dist and does not need it committed.
frontend/build/
# .agents/memory: per-repl agent working memory; both repls mutate it
# independently (the index + topic files), so it must not sync.
.agents/memory/
